	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-WL05320006_01.jpg"/>
			<p><note type="gloss">stamp on the left:</note> Committee to Collect Material</p>
			<p>about the Destruction of <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term> Jewry <date when="1939">1939</date></p>

			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_blumberg_leyb">Blumberg Leyb</persName></p>
			<p>Born in <date when="1915">1915</date>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName></p>

			<p>Testimony number 6</p>

			<p>(recorded on <date when="1939-11-16">16th November, 1939</date>)</p>

			<p>I <note type="gloss">There are no personal pronouns and no auxiliary verbs in the record (probably in order to save time), so it’s
					impossible to know if it is the 1st or the 3rd person.</note> left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html"
					>Warsaw</placeName> on <date when="1939-10-14">14th October</date>. Before, I had been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hidden</term> all the time on <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Bonifraterska street 4</placeName>. I didn’t see any scenes. The house was not
				damaged by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1083" type="subject">bombings</term>.</p>
			<p>I reached <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName> by the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765328/malkinia-gorna.html">Małkinia</placeName> – <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776069/bialystok.html">Białystok</placeName> road. I went on foot, in the company of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term> workers who were going to the <term
					type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviets</term>. There was also a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term> from the region of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName>. We got through safely, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> did not bother us.</p>
			<p>I heard a lot of stories, but don’t remember any.</p>
			<p>The border was open, we reached <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName> without
				difficulties.</p>
		</body>
